<h1 id="io-socket-request-">io.socket.request()</h1>
<p>Sends a virtual request to a Sails server using Socket.io.</p>
<p>This function is very similar to <code>io.socket.get()</code>, <code>io.socket.post()</code>, etc. except that it provides lower-level access to the request headers, parameters, method, and URL of the request.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>This function is provided by the <code>sails.io.js</code> JavaScript client, and is accessible in the <strong>browser</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id="usage" permalink="usage">Usage</h3>
<pre><code data-language="javascript">io.socket.request(options, function (data, jwr)){
  // ...
  // jwr.headers
  // jwr.statusCode
  // jwr.body === data
  // ...
});
</code></pre><!-- __LANG=%%__ -->
<h3 id="example" permalink="example">Example</h3>
<pre><code data-language="javascript">io.socket.request({
  method: &apos;get&apos;,
  url: &apos;/user/3/friends&apos;,
  params: {},
  headers: {}
})
</code></pre><!-- __LANG=%%__ -->
